      "titleText": "🚨 Incident Response Lifecycle",
      "titleColor": "#00ff41",
      "titleSize": 48,
      "subtitleText": "",
      "subtitleColor": "#2a6b3a",
      "bodyText": "Reference: NIST SP 800-61r2",
      "bodyColor": "#7ab87a",
      "bodySize": 22,
      "bullets": [],
      "tableData": {
        "headers": [],
        "rows": []
      },
      "codeText": "1. Preparation     → Build playbooks, deploy logging, train the team\n2. Detection       → Identify indicators of compromise (IOCs)\n3. Containment     → Short-term (isolate host) and long-term (patch, block)\n4. Eradication     → Remove malware, revoke credentials, close access\n5. Recovery        → Restore services, verify integrity, monitor closely\n6. Lessons Learned → Post-incident review, update playbooks and detections",
      "codeLang": "",
      "imageUrl": "",
