    {
      "id": "ec0c3139-3829-4d14-87f4-31576ea79105",
      "layout": "top",
      "bgType": "gradient",
      "bgColor": "#080b08",
      "bgGradient": "linear-gradient(160deg,#020602 0%,#040d04 100%)",
      "bgImage": "",
      "titleText": "Ransomware",
      "titleColor": "#00ff41",
      "titleSize": 36,
      "subtitleText": "",
      "subtitleColor": "#2a6b3a",
      "bodyText": "",
      "bodyColor": "#7ab87a",
      "bodySize": 22,
      "bullets": [],
      "tableData": {
        "headers": [],
        "rows": []
      },
      "codeText": "1. IMMEDIATE: Isolate affected hosts from network (disable NIC, not shutdown)\n2. Preserve memory dump before shutdown (lsass, suspicious processes)\n3. Identify patient zero — check file creation timestamps\n4. Check for lateral movement — event logs, network flow data\n5. Identify data exfiltration — DLP logs, proxy/firewall egress\n6. Identify ransomware family — submit sample to ID-Ransomware (https://id-ransomware.malwarehunterteam.com)\n7. Determine if decryptor exists (https://www.nomoreransom.org)\n8. Scope full affected systems — check all hosts for encrypted files, indicators\n9. Eradicate: rebuild from clean backups (verify backups pre-date infection)\n10. Recover and monitor closely for re-infection",
      "codeLang": "",
      "imageUrl": "",
      "showTitle": true,
      "showSubtitle": false,
      "showBody": false,
      "showBullets": false,
      "showTable": false,
      "showCode": true,
      "showImage": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "fontFamily": "'Courier New', 'Fira Mono', monospace",
      "transition": "fade"
    },
    {
      "id": "21d291f3-b0f5-4b40-9f65-a723c5ed8216",
      "layout": "top",
      "bgType": "gradient",
      "bgColor": "#080b08",
      "bgGradient": "linear-gradient(160deg,#020602 0%,#040d04 100%)",
      "bgImage": "",
      "titleText": "Account Compromise",
      "titleColor": "#00ff41",
      "titleSize": 36,
      "subtitleText": "",
      "subtitleColor": "#2a6b3a",
      "bodyText": "",
      "bodyColor": "#7ab87a",
      "bodySize": 22,
      "bullets": [],
      "tableData": {
        "headers": [],
        "rows": []
      },
      "codeText": "1. Disable compromised account immediately\n2. Force password reset on all related accounts (shared passwords)\n3. Revoke all active sessions and OAuth tokens\n4. Check mailbox rules (auto-forwarding to external address is common)\n5. Review MFA registrations — attacker may have added their own device\n6. Audit email forwards and calendar sharing\n7. Check sent items and deleted items for data exfiltration\n8. Review sign-in logs for IP/device/location patterns\n9. Scope: check for lateral movement using compromised credentials\n10. Harden: enforce MFA, conditional access, credential monitoring",
      "codeLang": "",
      "imageUrl": "",
      "showTitle": true,
      "showSubtitle": false,
      "showBody": false,
      "showBullets": false,
      "showTable": false,
      "showCode": true,
      "showImage": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "fontFamily": "'Courier New', 'Fira Mono', monospace",
      "transition": "fade"
    },
    {
      "id": "e301d671-5be3-4123-8fec-03517634628a",
      "layout": "top",
      "bgType": "gradient",
      "bgColor": "#080b08",
      "bgGradient": "linear-gradient(160deg,#020602 0%,#040d04 100%)",
      "bgImage": "",
      "titleText": "Malware / C2 Beacon",
      "titleColor": "#00ff41",
      "titleSize": 36,
      "subtitleText": "",
      "subtitleColor": "#2a6b3a",
      "bodyText": "",
      "bodyColor": "#7ab87a",
      "bodySize": 22,
      "bullets": [],
      "tableData": {
        "headers": [],
        "rows": []
      },
      "codeText": "1. Identify all affected hosts via C2 IOC (IP, domain, hash, JA3)\n2. Capture memory from affected hosts before isolation\n3. Isolate: remove from network, keep powered on for analysis\n4. Identify persistence mechanisms (scheduled tasks, services, registry run keys)\n5. Determine implant capability (keylogging, screenshot, lateral movement, exfil)\n6. Review 90-day log history for dwell time and full scope\n7. Eradicate: remove all persistence, rebuild compromised hosts\n8. Reset credentials accessed from or on compromised hosts\n9. Block IOCs at perimeter (firewall, proxy, DNS sinkhole)\n10. Improve detections based on observed TTPs",
      "codeLang": "",
      "imageUrl": "",
      "showTitle": true,
      "showSubtitle": false,
      "showBody": false,
      "showBullets": false,
      "showTable": false,
      "showCode": true,
      "showImage": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "fontFamily": "'Courier New', 'Fira Mono', monospace",
      "transition": "fade"
    },
